    {
        "id": "full-stack-flow",
        "type": "tab",
        "label": "Full Stack API Example",
        "disabled": false,
        "info": "## Full Stack API Example\n\nThis flow demonstrates all security and data layers working together:\n- **TLS/HTTPS**: Secure transport on port 3443\n- **OAuth2**: Client credentials authentication via Keycloak\n- **OPA**: Policy-based authorization\n- **SQL Server**: Database persistence for CRUD operations\n\n### How It Works\n\nAll layers are truly integrated:\n1. Request arrives over HTTPS (TLS)\n2. JWT token validated against Keycloak JWKS\n3. OPA policy checked for authorization\n4. SQL Server query executed automatically\n\n### Endpoints\n\n| Method | Path | Auth | Permission | SQL |\n|--------|------|------|------------|-----|\n| GET | /api/v1/public/health | None | None | None |\n| GET | /api/v1/products | Required | user | SELECT |\n| GET | /api/v1/products/:id | Required | user | SELECT WHERE |\n| POST | /api/v1/products | Required | admin | INSERT |\n| PUT | /api/v1/products/:id | Required | admin | UPDATE |\n| DELETE | /api/v1/products/:id | Required | admin | DELETE |\n\n### Service Accounts\n\n- `my-api-client` (user role): api:read, api:write\n- `my-admin-service` (admin role): api:read, api:write, api:delete, api:admin\n\n### Testing\n\n```bash\n# Get token for user service\nTOKEN=$(curl -s -X POST \\\n  'http://localhost:8080/realms/my-realm/protocol/openid-connect/token' \\\n  -d 'client_id=my-api-client' \\\n  -d 'client_secret=my-client-secret' \\\n  -d 'grant_type=client_credentials' \\\n  | jq -r '.access_token')\n\n# List products (requires api:read) - queries SQL Server\ncurl -k -H \"Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN\" \\\n  https://localhost:3443/api/v1/products\n```"
    },
